{
  "texts": [
    "The anomaly probability is 0 at the centre and tends towards 1, as it approaches either of the boundaries.",
    "The x-axis is range of probability distribution and y-axis, its frequency.For the example with n = 3, we have T = 36, P(sen n l) = 3/36 = 0.083 and P(sen n r) = 31/36 = 0.861.",
    "The center of the probability distribution is p = 0.5.",
    "The anomaly probability for sen is computed using Equation (5).",
    "The edge cases are shown in Algorithm 3."
